
                           Healing

     One of the main activities in mudding is engaging in wild killing.
However, in the process of your wild slaying, you might actually get
hurt.  After all, the monsters occasionally actually hit back.  In the
event that this happens and you decide to try to avoid death, it might
help to know how to heal.  There are a number of different ways of doing
this, including waiting, drinking, eating, and magical healing.

     Waiting around is the most boring way of healing.  That's because
just standing around waiting to heal heals you VERY slowly.  One hit
point every so often.  At that rate it can take quite a while to get up
to full.

     Drinking alcohol is the most common way of speeding up healing.
By drinking, not only do you forget your troubles, you get intoxicated.
While intoxicated you heal at six hit points every so often.  Also,
if the drink that you down is strong enough, then you will get some
instant healing.  This is very useful if you are in a fight and don't
want to have to flee yet.  You only have so much drinking capacity.  The
higher your level, the more you can drink before you are smashed and
have to wait and sober up before you can drink more.

     Eating works much the same as drinking, except that all of the
healing is instant healing.  Your healing rate doesn't speed up.  Like
with drinking, you can only do so much.  Higher level means bigger
stomach.

     Besides food and drink, there is also magical healing.  Some guilds
can use their spell points to heal their hit points.  Also, some
magical items heal hit points when used.

